'''Alicja Kornasiewicz''' (born March 19, 1951 in [[Kańczuga]])<ref name="orka">[http://orka.sejm.gov.pl/ArchAll2.nsf/X/201 Posłowie X kadencji 1989 - 1991], archive of the Polish Sejm (in Polish)</ref> is a Polish economist, manager and politician. She was a member of [[Sejm of the Republic of Poland|Polish parliament]] and served as [[Secretary of State]] and Vice Minister at the [[Ministry of State Treasury (Poland)|Ministry of State Treasury]] in Poland. She is a managing director of the Warsaw office of [[Morgan Stanley]].
==Biography== Kornasiewicz studied at [[Warsaw School of Economics|Szkoła Główna Planowania i Statystyki]].<ref name="orka"/> She received a PhD degree from [[Poznań University of Economics]].{{fact|date=October 2018}} 1978 she passed exams as [[Statutory auditor]]; she is a member of the ''National Chamber of Statutory Auditors'' in Poland.{{fact|date=October 2018}} She attended the six-week Advanced Management Programme at [[Harvard Business School]] and the Executive and Advanced Management Programme at [[INSEAD]].{{fact|date=October 2018}}
At the [[History of Poland (1989–present)|first free elections]] after the [[Democratization|democratic transition]] in Poland, Kornasiewicz became a member of parliament from 1989 to 1991, representing the [[Polish People's Party]] (election district of [[Płock]]).<ref name="orka"/> In the government of [[Jerzy Buzek]] she served as Secretary of State in the Polish Ministry of the Treasury from 1997 to 2000.{{fact|date=October 2018}}
Prior to that she worked for the [[European Bank for Reconstruction and Development]] (EBRD) as a senior banker in London. Kornasiewicz was head of emerging European countries investment banking at [[Unicredit Group]] and a member of the Executive Committee at the bank’s ''Markets & Investment Banking Division''. From 2010 she was [[CEO]] of Polish [[Bank Pekao SA]].{{fact|date=October 2018}}
In January 2012 Kornasiewicz joined Morgan Stanley as a senior adviser in investment banking covering Poland and [[Central and Eastern Europe]] (CEE). She is a managing director of the Warsaw office of the firm. Kornasiewicz is a jury member at [[Galeria Chwały Polskiej Ekonomii]].<ref>[http://www.finexa.org/aktualnosci/41,jury_prestizowej_nagrody_galeria_chwaly_polskiej_ekonomii_skompletowane?goback=.gmp_3962130.gfl_3962130.gde_3962130_member_213704522.gmp_3962130.gde_3962130_member_249896091 Press release] from June 14, 2013, website Finexa (in Polish)</ref>
